@@eShadowmere -- Prism Archive, Founding Precedent@@N

Shadowmere is the reason the founding charter exists. Not the only
reason -- but the @@rworking demonstration@@N of every principle Kiess
was built to reject. When Three-Power Governance debates whether a
policy has gone too far, someone says: @@d"Check Shadowmere."@@N

Midgaard founded Shadowmere as a frontier march-town: guard transit,
tax goods, process the dead before they reached core districts.
Practical mandate. Sound logistics.

Then came the @@rPlague Mandate@@N. Emergency directives authorized
rapid intake, forced quarantines, cremation powers, suspension of
lineage appeals. @@rTemporary became permanent.@@N No authority agreed on
rollback. The @@rLast Bell Crisis@@N saw three contradictory decrees
rung in one night: amnesty, lockdown, requisition. The city
calcified into mutually hostile systems.

This is the @@yfounding case@@N. Every element of Three-Power Governance
was designed as a countermeasure to Shadowmere's failure:

@@WThe Compact Temples@@N hold sanctuary law but cannot issue quarantine
orders -- preventing the deadlock that paralyzed Shadowmere's rites.

@@yThe Trade Syndics@@N hold market authority but cannot conscript or
seize goods without Wall Command countersignature -- preventing the
requisition spiral that stripped Shadowmere's merchants.

@@dWall Command@@N holds gate discipline but cannot extend emergency
powers beyond one lunar cycle without Syndic and Temple renewal --
preventing the permanent emergency that turned garrison into
occupation.

And above all: @@y"No sealed warrant from a predecessor authority
shall bind a Kiess citizen."@@N Because Shadowmere's five factions --
the @@WOathbound March@@N executing obsolete orders, the @@rCrimson
Household@@N claiming bloodline, the @@dBinder Collegium@@N treating souls
as ledger entries, the @@rGallows Syndicate@@N monetizing execution, the
@@eFen-Adapted Remnants@@N proving ecology outlasts governance -- all
still invoke law. All still stamp, witness, and seal. All are
@@rwrong@@N.

Shadowmere is what happens when lawful systems become predatory
under emergency powers without sunset. Kiess reads that sentence
at every founding anniversary, carved into the Prism's eastern face.

@@rEmergency powers without sunset are poison.@@N We wrote that in
stone so we would not forget.
